	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2784397878" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2784397878" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>I think I know why: "isXmlHttpRequest()" works if your JavaScript library sets an X-Requested-With HTTP header. It is known to work with common JavaScript frameworks. But if this header wasn't passed - it won't work, so you need to add another custom check for it.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
